{"title":"#Vanlife – Quigley 4×4 adds 2″ lift kit for 2WD, AWD Ford Transit","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/23/vanlife-quigley-4x4-adds-2-lift-kit-for-2wd-awd-ford-transit/","date":1629758118000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Now there’s another option for lifting your Ford Transit camper van. Quigley, the brand most know as that 4×4 conversion kit company for Sprinters, Transits, and full size vans, has just launched their Q-Lift 2″ kit for Ford Transits.</p><p>The kit drops the entire sub frame under the engine, which includes spacers, but also a lot of brackets and other parts. That’s because simply adding spacers wouldn’t address the differences in axle lengths, placements, and shaft angles on the AWD model.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23182740/quigley-qlift-2-inch-spacer-lift-kit-for-ford-transit-awd-2wd-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23182740/quigley-qlift-2-inch-spacer-lift-kit-for-ford-transit-awd-2wd-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x363/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"quigley q lift kit for ford transit camper vans\" width=\"900\" height=\"675\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23182740/quigley-qlift-2-inch-spacer-lift-kit-for-ford-transit-awd-2wd-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 900w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23182740/quigley-qlift-2-inch-spacer-lift-kit-for-ford-transit-awd-2wd-2-297x223.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23182740/quigley-qlift-2-inch-spacer-lift-kit-for-ford-transit-awd-2wd-2-800x600.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23182740/quigley-q